15/02/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- War Crimes Prosecutor Vladimir Vukcevic said on Monday (February 14th) he will meet with prosecutors from Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Croatia to discuss the case of Croatian war veteran Tihomir Purda. The meeting is scheduled for Thursday in Bijeljina, BiH. Purda was arrested in early January at the border between Croatia and BiH based on a Serbian arrest warrant. Belgrade suspects him of involvement in 1991 war crimes committed against Serbs in Vukovar. (Beta, Radio Free Europe, RTS - 14/02/11)
